1
00:01:16,040 --> 00:01:16,840
Uncle Jimei

2
00:01:17,319 --> 00:01:18,359
I've got something to tell you.

3
00:01:18,359 --> 00:01:19,599
What's the rush?

4
00:01:21,400 --> 00:01:21,920
Let me show you.

5
00:01:22,280 --> 00:01:23,840
This is our new guest today.

6
00:01:24,040 --> 00:01:25,439
The food blogger I told you about.

7
00:01:25,439 --> 00:01:26,239
Ms. Nana.

8
00:01:26,480 --> 00:01:27,680
She's got millions of followers.

9
00:01:28,519 --> 00:01:30,079
But she's a real picky eater.

10
00:01:30,400 --> 00:01:31,599
She says she hates eating ginger.

11
00:01:31,959 --> 00:01:34,560
Says it feels like sand in her mouth.

12
00:01:34,840 --> 00:01:36,239
But she really loves the flavor of ginger.

13
00:01:36,239 --> 00:01:37,159
Isn't that just weird?

14
00:01:37,640 --> 00:01:39,680
Then I'll just strain it one more time.

15
00:01:41,040 --> 00:01:42,120
How many times have you strained it?

16
00:01:42,560 --> 00:01:43,200
Third time.

17
00:01:44,079 --> 00:01:44,719
Third time?

18
00:01:44,959 --> 00:01:46,000
Milk warms the stomach,

19
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:47,040
but ginger stings the heart.

20
00:01:47,599 --> 00:01:48,439
She wants the warmth,

21
00:01:49,079 --> 00:01:49,799
not the sting.

22
00:01:50,599 --> 00:01:51,760
I have no idea what you're saying.

23
00:01:53,200 --> 00:01:53,560
Oh, right.

24
00:01:53,760 --> 00:01:54,879
Meiduo also told me

25
00:01:55,040 --> 00:01:56,280
that just now on the back hill,

26
00:01:56,400 --> 00:01:58,640
she stopped two hikers digging up wild gastrodia.

27
00:01:59,040 --> 00:02:01,200
Isn't she just beautiful inside and out?

28
00:02:01,280 --> 00:02:02,319
I'm totally a fan.

29
00:02:09,240 --> 00:02:09,919
Uncle Jimei?

30
00:02:11,639 --> 00:02:12,280
It's nothing.

31
00:02:26,400 --> 00:02:27,360
I turned off the stove.

32
00:02:31,240 --> 00:02:32,280
Yak Milk Ginger Curd,

33
00:02:33,680 --> 00:02:34,199
to ward off the cold.

34
00:02:34,680 --> 00:02:36,520
A Cantonese dessert with a Tibetan twist.

35
00:02:36,879 --> 00:02:37,800
This is genius!

36
00:02:40,080 --> 00:02:41,080
I'll bring it over to her.

37
00:03:14,080 --> 00:03:14,800
Ms. Nana

38
00:03:14,919 --> 00:03:16,400
This is Uncle Jimei's new creation.

39
00:03:16,560 --> 00:03:17,479
Yak Milk Ginger Curd.

40
00:03:17,840 --> 00:03:19,000
He was so meticulous making it.

41
00:03:19,319 --> 00:03:21,080
He even strained the ginger juice three times.

42
00:03:22,240 --> 00:03:23,000
Three times!

43
00:03:23,080 --> 00:03:23,599
Yeah.

44
00:03:23,919 --> 00:03:24,960
I was like, is that really necessary?

45
00:03:24,960 --> 00:03:25,840
Isn't that funny?

46
00:03:26,280 --> 00:03:26,759
Go on, try it.

47
00:03:42,879 --> 00:03:43,439
How is it?

48
00:03:50,599 --> 00:03:51,360
Uncle Jimei,

49
00:03:52,080 --> 00:03:52,719
I'm back.

50
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:54,719
Here, this is for you.

51
00:03:55,400 --> 00:03:56,719
Thanks, Uncle Jimei.

52
00:03:56,960 --> 00:03:58,479
I almost couldn't resist earlier.

53
00:03:58,479 --> 00:03:59,199
I was about to eat it.

54
00:03:59,680 --> 00:04:00,000
By the way,

55
00:04:00,120 --> 00:04:01,560
Ms. Nana asked me to thank you.

56
00:04:01,759 --> 00:04:04,400
She said this Yak Milk Ginger Curd is delicious.

57
00:04:04,639 --> 00:04:05,199
She said

58
00:04:07,159 --> 00:04:09,159
she had this same flavor as a kid.

59
00:04:09,520 --> 00:04:10,800
She hasn't had it in 20 years.

60
00:04:11,199 --> 00:04:12,240
She's so dramatic.

61
00:04:12,240 --> 00:04:13,439
Hasn't had it in 20 years?

62
00:04:13,560 --> 00:04:14,639
How old is she even?

63
00:04:17,439 --> 00:04:18,000
Did she...

64
00:04:18,879 --> 00:04:19,920
say anything else?

65
00:04:20,360 --> 00:04:21,199
Nothing much.

66
00:04:22,040 --> 00:04:22,360
Oh, right.

67
00:04:22,519 --> 00:04:23,279
She said tonight

68
00:04:23,360 --> 00:04:24,560
she'll come to our concert.

69
00:04:33,319 --> 00:04:34,079
So good, so good, so good!

70
00:07:00,839 --> 00:07:02,000
Thank you, everyone.

71
00:07:06,240 --> 00:07:07,639
Okay, let's take a break.

72
00:07:09,759 --> 00:07:11,120
How was it, Dr. Meiduo?

73
00:07:11,120 --> 00:07:12,199
Here to complain about the noise?

74
00:07:12,879 --> 00:07:14,360
That was the plan.

75
00:07:15,079 --> 00:07:16,560
But after listening, I think...

76
00:07:16,560 --> 00:07:17,040
it's not bad.

77
00:07:19,759 --> 00:07:21,000
Then come on in. Let's go.

78
00:07:23,959 --> 00:07:24,519
Come on.

79
00:07:25,439 --> 00:07:26,000
Thanks.

80
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:26,800
Hello, Dr. Meiduo.

81
00:07:28,519 --> 00:07:29,839
You sang really well just now.

82
00:07:31,240 --> 00:07:32,040
Even Meiduo said it was okay.

83
00:07:32,759 --> 00:07:33,920
I was just checking my...

84
00:07:33,920 --> 00:07:34,360
vlog's

85
00:07:34,360 --> 00:07:35,480
comment section.

86
00:07:35,480 --> 00:07:37,839
Many say Nyingchi is a food desert.

87
00:07:38,279 --> 00:07:40,079
Besides Stone Pot Chicken and Tibetan Scented Pig,

88
00:07:40,079 --> 00:07:41,560
they get sick of it after two meals.

89
00:07:42,079 --> 00:07:42,959
Well, they're not wrong.

90
00:07:44,240 --> 00:07:45,160
Meiduo,

91
00:07:45,319 --> 00:07:46,879
can't you be a bit nicer?

92
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:49,680
Is telling the truth wrong?

93
00:07:52,319 --> 00:07:52,800
Right.

94
00:07:53,399 --> 00:07:54,920
But we've got Jimei, don't we?

95
00:07:55,480 --> 00:07:56,279
Right, right, right.

96
00:07:56,560 --> 00:07:58,759
Uncle Jimei is working on new fusion dishes.

97
00:07:58,959 --> 00:07:59,399
Really?

98
00:08:05,279 --> 00:08:06,399
Here you are. Enjoy.

99
00:08:13,199 --> 00:08:14,560
This looks pretty good.

100
00:08:14,800 --> 00:08:15,800
I'd say it rivals Michelin.

101
00:08:16,319 --> 00:08:16,720
Qianqian,

102
00:08:17,360 --> 00:08:18,399
find a time to promote this.

103
00:08:20,839 --> 00:08:22,600
We do need to promote it,

104
00:08:23,279 --> 00:08:24,920
but there are so many trolls online now.

105
00:08:25,199 --> 00:08:26,879
Me saying it's good won't cut it.

106
00:08:28,480 --> 00:08:30,319
You need someone with real clout

107
00:08:30,600 --> 00:08:31,639
and a really picky palate,

108
00:08:31,639 --> 00:08:32,159
an influencer,

109
00:08:32,279 --> 00:08:33,840
to livestream eating it on site.

110
00:08:34,240 --> 00:08:35,519
Where would we find that?

111
00:08:37,879 --> 00:08:38,879
There's one right here,

112
00:08:38,879 --> 00:08:39,240
an influencer,

113
00:08:39,240 --> 00:08:39,960
and you can't see her?

114
00:08:47,080 --> 00:08:47,840
Ms. Nana!

115
00:08:48,840 --> 00:08:50,320
Ms. Nana, please help us.

116
00:09:04,200 --> 00:09:04,960
Uncle Jimei,

117
00:09:10,639 --> 00:09:11,639
this little seal...

118
00:09:13,159 --> 00:09:14,360
I saw one as a child.

119
00:09:16,039 --> 00:09:16,919
Back then,

120
00:09:17,840 --> 00:09:18,600
there was someone

121
00:09:19,399 --> 00:09:20,759
who made me the very same treat

122
00:09:21,240 --> 00:09:22,159
to cheer me up.

123
00:09:24,639 --> 00:09:25,559
He said

124
00:09:26,480 --> 00:09:28,480
it was a magic trick by Sun Wukong.

125
00:09:31,360 --> 00:09:32,039
Later,

126
00:09:33,519 --> 00:09:34,879
I never saw him again.

127
00:09:41,480 --> 00:09:42,639
Qianqian told me

128
00:09:44,320 --> 00:09:45,200
you're just like me,

129
00:09:45,679 --> 00:09:46,519
also from Guangdong.

130
00:09:48,879 --> 00:09:50,120
So here in Peach Blossom Village,

131
00:09:50,120 --> 00:09:51,399
you must've been here for years.

132
00:09:53,840 --> 00:09:54,720
Here,

133
00:09:55,840 --> 00:09:56,759
cooking food,

134
00:09:57,559 --> 00:09:58,519
enjoying the scenery,

135
00:10:01,720 --> 00:10:03,039
you feel settled, don't you?

136
00:10:04,919 --> 00:10:06,840
But what about those you abandoned?

137
00:10:08,120 --> 00:10:10,000
Do you know what they went through?

138
00:10:11,759 --> 00:10:13,799
You're nothing but an irresponsible scumbag.

139
00:10:17,519 --> 00:10:18,320
Ms. Nana.

140
00:10:19,039 --> 00:10:19,759
I want to file a complaint.

141
00:10:20,559 --> 00:10:21,360
A complaint?

142
00:10:21,639 --> 00:10:23,639
From now on, get a different cook for my meals.

143
00:10:24,559 --> 00:10:25,480
I... I... I...

144
00:11:02,039 --> 00:11:03,320
Are you here to comfort me?

145
00:11:04,840 --> 00:11:05,440
No.

146
00:11:07,720 --> 00:11:08,600
Then why are you here?

147
00:11:12,960 --> 00:11:14,919
This is a great spot for stargazing.

148
00:11:17,879 --> 00:11:19,080
You're quite interesting.

149
00:11:21,200 --> 00:11:22,399
A lot of people say that.

150
00:11:27,399 --> 00:11:29,840
Is that the Big Dipper over there?

151
00:11:32,279 --> 00:11:33,919
Tibetans call it the Seven Brothers.

152
00:11:34,240 --> 00:11:35,320
Seven Brothers.

153
00:11:37,840 --> 00:11:40,480
Legend says they vowed to never part.

154
00:11:40,720 --> 00:11:42,159
And later they turned into stars.

155
00:11:43,480 --> 00:11:44,879
One linked to the next.

156
00:11:48,559 --> 00:11:50,120
Never to be parted.

157
00:11:52,120 --> 00:11:54,000
What if someone lets go first?

158
00:12:00,519 --> 00:12:01,559
Then just take their hand again.

159
00:12:24,519 --> 00:12:25,200
Oh, it's you.

160
00:12:28,320 --> 00:12:29,320
Sorry you had to see that.

161
00:12:31,360 --> 00:12:32,320
It's nothing, really.

162
00:12:35,559 --> 00:12:37,480
Everyone's got something weighing on them.

163
00:12:39,519 --> 00:12:42,399
Some things, buried in your heart too long,

164
00:12:42,840 --> 00:12:43,799
once the wind blows,

165
00:12:44,440 --> 00:12:45,480
they just can't stay hidden.

166
00:12:50,240 --> 00:12:51,240
She's my daughter.

167
00:12:54,799 --> 00:12:55,840
Twenty years ago,

168
00:12:57,039 --> 00:12:58,080
I left them behind.

169
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:01,000
I know they hate me for it.

170
00:13:02,799 --> 00:13:04,080
But I never imagined

171
00:13:05,000 --> 00:13:05,879
that twenty years later,

172
00:13:06,799 --> 00:13:08,600
she'd find this place, and find me.

173
00:13:11,919 --> 00:13:12,919
Look at those mountains.

174
00:13:14,080 --> 00:13:15,759
They've stood there for tens of thousands of years.

175
00:13:16,679 --> 00:13:18,200
Clouds and mist,

176
00:13:18,759 --> 00:13:19,840
coming and going,

177
00:13:21,559 --> 00:13:22,919
but they never explain themselves.

178
00:13:25,600 --> 00:13:27,039
But after all these years,

179
00:13:28,559 --> 00:13:29,960
now that I want to explain,

180
00:13:30,519 --> 00:13:33,039
I really don't know where to start.

181
00:13:34,320 --> 00:13:36,039
Some things don't need explaining.

182
00:13:36,600 --> 00:13:38,480
When the time comes, you'll understand.

183
00:13:41,720 --> 00:13:42,399
It's freezing.

184
00:13:43,120 --> 00:13:44,080
I should head back.

185
00:13:48,720 --> 00:13:49,759
No, thanks, I'm fine.

186
00:13:49,840 --> 00:13:50,639
Take it.

187
00:13:51,200 --> 00:13:53,039
If you catch a cold, how will you livestream?

188
00:14:00,480 --> 00:14:01,279
I'm heading off.

189
00:14:02,240 --> 00:14:02,759
Goodbye.
